<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="572" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1704,2017]" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1848,1873]" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Remarks.</emphasis>
Widely distributed Holarctic species (Růžička 2015), recently confirmed from Alaska, Yukon and Northwest Territories, but not from the rest of North America (
<bibRefCitation box="[879,1080,1884,1909]" pageId="17" pageNumber="572" refId="ref25717" refString="Sikes, D. S., Trumbo, S. T. &amp; Peck, S. B. (2016) Cryptic diversity in the New world burying beetle fauna: Nicrophorus hebes Kirby; new status as a resurrected name (Coleoptera: Silphidae: Nicrophorinae). Arthropod Systematics &amp; Phylogeny, 74, 299 - 309." type="journal article">
Sikes 
<emphasis box="[950,1001,1884,1909]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). In central Europe, commonly found in forested habitats, most frequent in wet coniferous forests (
<bibRefCitation box="[938,1102,1920,1945]" pageId="17" pageNumber="572" refId="ref25092" refString="Ruzicka, J. (1994) Seasonal activity and habitat associations of Silphidae and Leiodidae: Cholevinae (Coleoptera) in central Bohemia. Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae, 58, 67 - 78." type="journal article">Růžička 1994</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1240,1920,1945]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, reported from a single record in 
<collectingRegion box="[334,561,1956,1981]" country="Turkey" name="Adiyaman" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Adıyaman Province</collectingRegion>
, belonging to the 
<collectingRegion box="[764,848,1957,1980]" country="American Samoa" name="Eastern" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Eastern</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry box="[855,952,1956,1981]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
Region (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1140,1956,1981]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–34" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1505,1528]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,195,1479]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,195,1484]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 33–34. Distribution of (33) Nicrophorus vespilloides and (34) N. vestigator in Turkey." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301594/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). Here we report a second record from 
<collectingRegion box="[291,375,1993,2016]" country="American Samoa" name="Eastern" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Eastern</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry box="[382,478,1992,2017]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
Region, which is the first record from 
<collectingRegion box="[914,1121,1992,2017]" country="Turkey" name="Ardahan" pageId="17" pageNumber="572">Ardahan Province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
